00:06:19.140 --> 00:06:23.060
Generalizability is not always perfect. And we'll get back to that later.

110
00:06:24.840 --> 00:06:25.540
Now, just

111
00:06:27.040 --> 00:06:30.260
a brief sidestep. So medical data is very diverse, right?

112
00:06:30.280 --> 00:06:34.160
You know that we can have pathology images, we can have MRIs, we can have CTs, we

113
00:06:34.180 --> 00:06:35.920
have lots of different modalities of data.

114
00:06:36.820 --> 00:06:40.780
And basically what we aim to do in our research and in our developments,

115
00:06:41.480 --> 00:06:45.400
we would love to be able to combine all these different modalities and

