121
00:07:04.600 --> 00:07:08.300
So we make a small sidestep. What we typically do in AI

122
00:07:08.440 --> 00:07:08.920
is we

123
00:07:09.940 --> 00:07:12.960
build representations of data, of data points,

124
00:07:14.660 --> 00:07:18.620
like you can see here. And this is if you use a large language model, an LLM,

125
00:07:18.780 --> 00:07:21.500
ChatGPT or Claude or one of these.

126
00:07:23.020 --> 00:07:23.330
Every

127
00:07:24.360 --> 00:07:25.040
data item

128
00:07:26.140 --> 00:07:29.800
will be translated into what we call an embedding or feature representation,

129
00:07:30.240 --> 00:07:31.560
which means we translate it into a

130
00:07:32.400 --> 00:07:36.280
vector of numbers. And in this case, woman could be some kind of vector

131
00:07:36.320 --> 00:07:39.300
of numbers, and suppose we would also have a man.

132
00:07:39.920 --> 00:07:43.400
And this is a bit artificial, but you could think of, we have many different

133
00:07:43.420 --> 00:07:47.260
characteristics of these data points that can be stored because they're relevant.

134
00:07:47.340 --> 00:07:48.510
For instance, in this case, you could say,

135
00:07:49.380 --> 00:07:53.000
how much does it resemble a living being? How much is it flying, human?

136
00:07:53.300 --> 00:07:57.280
What is the gender? So we can store data points

137
00:07:57.340 --> 00:08:00.480
in this large vector, and you can imagine that it's large

138
00:08:01.340 --> 00:08:05.240
array of numbers. You can also see this mathematically as a point in a

139
00:08:05.280 --> 00:08:08.760
high dimensional space. It's a bit sometimes difficult

140
00:08:08.800 --> 00:08:12.720
to visualize that. But actually, what we typically do is

141
00:08:12.760 --> 00:08:16.400
we take data points, and we put them in a vector of 700

142
00:08:16.440 --> 00:08:19.460
numbers, which basically means we have 700 dimensional space.

143
00:08:19.729 --> 00:08:22.820
Now, that's a lot, way too much to comprehend.

144
00:08:23.820 --> 00:08:27.460
But what you will often see in many of these examples is that we then project a

145
00:08:27.560 --> 00:08:31.300
space onto a plane, just to give you a bit of a feel for how well

146
00:08:31.640 --> 00:08:32.760
separations are possible.

147
00:08:33.841 --> 00:08:37.180
So, for instance, what we can say now is we have a way of

148
00:08:37.240 --> 00:08:40.660
representing the concept of a man, a woman, a king, a queen,

149
00:08:41.400 --> 00:08:43.680
and these can show up as points in the space.

150
00:08:44.720 --> 00:08:48.060
And if two points are closer together, it means they also resemble each other

151
00:08:48.080 --> 00:08:48.320
better.

152
00:08:49.280 --> 00:08:53.120
And if you do it as well, you can also start to even use these numbers to

153
00:08:53.400 --> 00:08:56.620
make calculations. So, for instance, what you could say now is if I have a queen,

154
00:08:56.760 --> 00:08:57.600
the concept of a queen,

155
00:08:58.620 --> 00:09:02.280
I take out gender, so I subtract woman from it, but I add man.

156
00:09:02.540 --> 00:09:06.000
I will arrive at a king because I changed the gender of the

157
00:09:06.320 --> 00:09:08.859
queen to become male, and now it's a king.

158
00:09:09.240 --> 00:09:13.020
So if you make these representations well, what you can do is actually they make

159
00:09:13.060 --> 00:09:14.600
sense, right? You can start to work with these.

160
00:09:15.900 --> 00:09:19.630
And moreover, what we can do is we can add context, and this is what happens a lot,

161
00:09:19.700 --> 00:09:21.260
for instance, in large language models.

162
00:09:21.920 --> 00:09:25.900
So suppose we would have the concept of a fruit and of technology, and now I

163
00:09:25.940 --> 00:09:29.580
have an apple in the context of what are the health benefits of

164
00:09:29.620 --> 00:09:29.960
apple.

165
00:09:31.000 --> 00:09:34.320
Now, this would mean that the context tells me that in this case, apple is

166
00:09:34.340 --> 00:09:38.160
something close to fruit, while if I would have a context like what is the share

167
00:09:38.220 --> 00:09:41.720
price of Apple, it would probably be something like technology.

168
00:09:42.200 --> 00:09:43.720
So we can use context to

169
00:09:44.560 --> 00:09:46.200
change these representations slightly.

170
00:09:46.780 --> 00:09:50.340
It also means if I am in pathology, I have part of an image, some region of an

171
00:09:50.360 --> 00:09:54.300
image. Regions around it in the tissue can help

172
00:09:54.340 --> 00:09:56.720
me to understand what that region is about, right?

173
00:09:56.800 --> 00:10:00.780
So also there, the context can help me to understand how to use that

174
00:10:01.280 --> 00:10:01.660
embedding.

175
00:10:04.080 --> 00:10:07.680
Now, this was about text. A similar thing we started to do

176
00:10:07.840 --> 00:10:10.080
already 10, 15 years ago with images.

177
00:10:10.260 --> 00:10:13.940
So we can also have representations of images, which are pretty much the same as I

178
00:10:13.980 --> 00:10:17.240
just showed you for these words. So what we can do is we can

179
00:10:17.460 --> 00:10:21.400
train a neural network in this case, and a neural network can pick up

180
00:10:21.480 --> 00:10:22.800
all kinds of visual features

181
00:10:23.620 --> 00:10:26.640
and result in an embedding in this high dimensional space.

182
00:10:27.020 --> 00:10:29.860
And you can use that, let's say, that high dimensional space then to do, for

183
00:10:29.880 --> 00:10:31.300
instance, image classification.

184
00:10:32.060 --> 00:10:34.340
So in this case, we would find all kinds of visual features.

185
00:10:34.540 --> 00:10:37.940
We would get a point in the space, and that point in the space could help us to

186
00:10:37.960 --> 00:10:41.300
decide that this is Tweety. So again, here you can use these

187
00:10:41.520 --> 00:10:42.340
embeddings to

188
00:10:44.740 --> 00:10:47.600
analyze images, to analyze data points, and to represent data points.

189
00:10:49.820 --> 00:10:53.240
Now, one of the problems, I already mentioned it briefly, is

190
00:10:53.300 --> 00:10:54.030
generalization.

191
00:10:55.160 --> 00:10:56.270
Because if we would

192
00:10:57.500 --> 00:11:01.400
train a model like I just showed you, we have some embedding in the space,

193
00:11:02.640 --> 00:11:06.520
then the embedding could be very much specific to the data that we use

194
00:11:06.640 --> 00:11:07.260
to train it on.

195
00:11:08.110 --> 00:11:11.660
And this is a very nice study that shows that here they produced

196
00:11:11.740 --> 00:11:12.160
AI

197
00:11:12.980 --> 00:11:16.860
that can predict the subtype of breast cancer.

