00:12:26.610 --> 00:12:29.930
And what you can clearly see here is that CTranspath does a much better job.

217
00:12:30.170 --> 00:12:33.850
It's less sensitive to this bias in the data. It's actually more robust.

218
00:12:34.710 --> 00:12:37.490
And CTranspath and Uni are foundation models.

219
00:12:37.710 --> 00:12:41.690
So they have been trained slightly differently than just task specific, what I

220
00:12:41.730 --> 00:12:42.510
showed you so far.

221
00:12:44.550 --> 00:12:48.250
So if we look at what happened in AI over the last 20,

222
00:12:48.410 --> 00:12:52.250
30 years, in the 2000s, in machine learning, this

223
00:12:52.270 --> 00:12:55.300
feature space that I told you about, this embedding space, we would really

224
00:12:56.270 --> 00:12:59.030
let's say build it ourselves. We would think about the features ourselves.

225
00:12:59.090 --> 00:13:00.690
We would manually derive these features.

226
00:13:01.510 --> 00:13:05.170
In the 2010s, we would have deep learning, where we would use networks to learn

227
00:13:05.210 --> 00:13:07.330
features. But they were very much task specific.

228
00:13:08.050 --> 00:13:12.040
In the 2020s, we have foundation models, and foundation models try to build these

229
00:13:12.130 --> 00:13:12.590
features

230
00:13:13.990 --> 00:13:17.970
in a task independent manner. And I will show you how this works.

231
00:13:18.130 --> 00:13:20.910
So rather than having an image and training

