00:19:04.214 --> 00:19:07.374
In terms of parameters, it's actually quite small.

333
00:19:08.294 --> 00:19:11.894
And it has a very high score. And just to show you

334
00:19:12.394 --> 00:19:15.874
a couple of tasks that it can do. So they

335
00:19:15.914 --> 00:19:19.874
tested it on many different tasks, and for instance, it's very good

336
00:19:19.954 --> 00:19:22.644
at predicting KRAS mutations from H&amp;E slides.

337
00:19:23.354 --> 00:19:26.124
So basically what it means is we can give it an H&amp;E stained slide,

338
00:19:26.954 --> 00:19:30.274
no fancy stainings, no fancy molecular analysis,

339
00:19:31.054 --> 00:19:31.814
and it can already

