00:30:23.026 --> 00:30:26.865
transfer learning is great, but there is still a big difference between

531
00:30:26.946 --> 00:30:29.326
pictures of cats and dogs and cancer.

532
00:30:29.406 --> 00:30:33.146
So the models still need a relatively large amount of data to learn tissue-specific

533
00:30:33.206 --> 00:30:37.066
features. So if we can pre-train the models on histology-specific data,

534
00:30:37.326 --> 00:30:40.686
maybe we have better features, and we can do better transfer learning.

535
00:30:41.226 --> 00:30:44.706
Of course, we don't have millions of labeled histology images, but we have a large

536
00:30:44.766 --> 00:30:48.096
amount of unlabeled images, and this is where the self-supervised learning is

537
00:30:48.126 --> 00:30:48.706
coming to game.

538
00:30:49.626 --> 00:30:53.466
So the objective of self-supervised learning is to learn specific tissue

539
00:30:53.526 --> 00:30:57.106
representations that can be used for many different tasks.

540
00:30:57.146 --> 00:30:59.766
And we saw it from York. This is like a simplified version.

