00:31:15.926 --> 00:31:18.946
for histology data. It helps the model to understand what does it mean to be

548
00:31:18.986 --> 00:31:19.746
histology tissue.

549
00:31:20.896 --> 00:31:24.606
And then we can use this pre-trained encoder to extract features from the images.

550
00:31:25.206 --> 00:31:29.186
And encoders trained in this way, this

551
00:31:29.226 --> 00:31:30.526
is what we call the foundation model.

552
00:31:31.486 --> 00:31:34.286
And depending on the type of encoders we have, we're going to have different types

