00:31:34.326 --> 00:31:37.806
of foundational models. So we have patch level foundational models, which give you

554
00:31:37.846 --> 00:31:41.646
features for individual patches in the image, or we can also have a slide-level

555
00:31:41.686 --> 00:31:45.366
foundational models that give you a single feature vector for the whole slide

556
00:31:45.406 --> 00:31:48.666
image. So they already agglomerate information from individual patches and give you

557
00:31:48.706 --> 00:31:50.866
a single vector for a whole slide image.

558
00:31:51.896 --> 00:31:52.416
And these

559
00:31:53.406 --> 00:31:54.986
foundational model works only with the images.

560
00:31:55.046 --> 00:31:56.886
So they're like unimodal foundational models.

561
00:31:56.966 --> 00:31:59.986
But then we also have multimodal foundational models. We already saw the figure.

562
00:32:01.106 --> 00:32:05.076
Here, the idea is we want to combine images and additional modality,

563
00:32:05.186 --> 00:32:08.086
usually text, and we use it to learn better feature

