00:32:12.106 --> 00:32:16.006
back to this later. So usually, we use CLIP-style methods.

566
00:32:16.506 --> 00:32:17.826
So there is this contrastive learning.

567
00:32:17.906 --> 00:32:21.766
So the idea is the model have to learn text representation and image

568
00:32:21.826 --> 00:32:25.746
representation jointly in a way that it's going to map them in a feature space.

569
00:32:25.806 --> 00:32:29.126
So you want to find such a representation that a text and

570
00:32:29.205 --> 00:32:32.886
an image are close to the feature space, or images with similar text

571
00:32:32.926 --> 00:32:34.686
descriptions should be closer in a feature space.

572
00:32:35.326 --> 00:32:38.796
So basically, use the text information to learn better feature representations, and

573
00:32:38.826 --> 00:32:40.466
then again, you can use it as a feature encoder.

574
00:32:41.226 --> 00:32:45.146
And in pathology, we have majority models going to be a combination of

575
00:32:45.186 --> 00:32:48.106
images and text. So it's like visual language models, but we also have a

